comment.body:
> add it back to BoringSSL if need be.

I'd say it only needs to be if we want to keep supporting BoringSSL and Chromium. Do we? @dstebila ?@christianpaquin?

repo.name: boringssl
repo.description: Fork of BoringSSL that includes prototype quantum-resistant key exchange and authentication in the TLS handshake based on liboqs

comment.body: If I remember our last discussion correctly: we can support it on a best-effort basis; i.e., fix things when we notice them breaking (vs. full-fledge interop test). I did some interop testing recently between boringssl and openssl when I last updated the project in Dec 2022; but mainly using Kyber. We already provide a strong disclaimer in the README, we can add more details about the state of our interop testing.
